text.section:
Counties, municipalities, and nonprofit organizations may apply for grants under the Program for the following purposes:
To educate automobile drivers and pedestrians about methods to increase pedestrian safety;
To enhance efforts to enforce State and local motor vehicle laws that protect the safety of pedestrians;
To design or redesign intersections to increase pedestrian safety and access; and
To enhance safe pedestrian access to transit facilities as defined in § 3-101 of this article.
